A range widget allows dashboard viewers to filter the CRM Analytics dashboard results based on a range of values for a measure.
Drag the range widget to the dashboard canvas.
Select a Field screen appears, showing a list of all measure fields in the specified dataset.
Select the date field that you want to filter on.
Behind the scenes, CRM Analytics creates a query with the measure that you selected.
CRM Analytics adds the query to the query panel, but you canâ€™t reuse it in other widgets.
The Widget panel groups the widget properties into sections.
To customize the appearance of the widget, set the widget properties.
For example, to enable this widget to filter other faceted widgets, select Broadcast selections as facets.
You can set an initial selection that applies when the dashboard opens.
While viewing the dashboard, viewers can change the selection to filter the results differently.
title: Adding a Range Widget to CRM Analytics Dashboards
